---
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/Breadcrumbs.astro'
import Link from '@/components/Link.astro'
import PageHead from '@/components/PageHead.astro'
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout class="max-w-3xl">
  <PageHead slot="head" title="About" description="Jonathan Muhire — ML systems, robotics, and research infrastructure" />
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'About', icon: 'lucide:info' }]} />

  <section>
    <div class="min-w-full">
      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-medium mb-8">About</h1>
        
        <p>
          I'm Jonathan Muhire — a CS & AI researcher building learning systems for real-world robots. I work across the
          full stack of ML research: from hardware teleoperation and data collection, to distributed storage infrastructure,
          to training and evaluation pipelines. I have 19 open-source repositories with working demos, real benchmarks, and
          production-grade code.
        </p>

        <p>
          Previously, I co-founded <strong>Neotix Robotics</strong>, where I built teleoperation and manipulation systems
          from scratch. I'm a <strong>Google Summer of Code 2025</strong> contributor, working on document AI pipelines for
          Renaissance manuscript digitization. I study Computer Science at Oklahoma Christian University.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mt-10 mb-4">What I Work On</h2>
        
        <p>
          My research sits at the intersection of embodied AI, data infrastructure, and systems engineering. I don't just
          train models — I build the entire pipeline around them.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">Robotics & Embodied AI</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/custom_pymycobot" external>Bimanual teleoperation</Link> — 
            Custom leader-follower system with real-time 7-DOF joint synchronization for imitation learning data collection.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/G1Humanoid-spinkick" external>Humanoid locomotion</Link> — 
            RL policy trained in MuJoCo for dynamic Unitree G1 motion including a full 360-degree spin kick.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/swarm-robotics-simulator" external>Swarm robotics</Link> — 
            Multi-agent simulation with flocking, foraging, and formation algorithms demonstrating emergent collective behavior.
          </li>
          <li>
            LeRobot ISO-101 platform — Local data-collection and policy-training workflow for fast experiment loops.
          </li>
          <li>
            UMI multi-sensor extraction and trajectory analysis with ORB-SLAM-based tracking.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">ML Research & Agents</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/agentic" external>Agentic Long-Runner</Link> — 
            ReAct agent with 4 memory modes. Needle-in-haystack evals show chunked vector retrieval fully recovers
            performance on 5,000+ word documents (0% → 100%).
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/RenAIssance-GSoC-2025" external>RenAIssance (GSoC 2025)</Link> — 
            Document AI pipeline for Renaissance-era texts: layout detection with LayoutLMv3, OCR, and post-correction.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/ArtExtract" external>ArtExtract</Link> — 
            CNN-RNN architecture for artwork classification with confusion matrix validation and training curves.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/cfn-biomed-eval" external>CFN Biomedical Eval</Link> — 
            Token-level and span-level benchmarks for clinical concept extraction.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/ISSR" external>ISSR</Link> — 
            Crisis detection system using NLP, sentiment analysis, and geospatial signal processing.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/pacman_ai" external>Pacman AI</Link> — 
            Autonomous agents with search algorithms and gameplay heuristics.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">Infrastructure & Systems</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/minio" external>MinIO + LakeFS</Link> — 
            3-node distributed cluster with erasure coding, data versioning, AIStor cache, and Prometheus + Grafana monitoring.
          </li>
          <li>
            Docker-based deployment pipelines for reproducible ML experiments.
          </li>
          <li>
            Dataset annotation workflows for manipulation episodes (gripper-pose, keyframe labeling).
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">Full-Stack & Mobile</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/medisync" external>MediSync</Link> — 
            Health records platform with scheduling, patient data, and clinical workflows.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/Agrifinance" external>AgriFinance</Link> — 
            Financial services for smallholder farmers with credit scoring and mobile-first design.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/ConnectFarm" external>ConnectFarm</Link> — 
            Agricultural marketplace connecting farmers to buyers.
          </li>
          <li>
            <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321/CampusBuddy_V1" external>CampusBuddy</Link> — 
            Flutter app for campus events, dining, and student resources.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mt-10 mb-4">Technical Stack</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Languages:</strong> Python, C++, Java, Dart, JavaScript<br/>
          <strong>ML/DL:</strong> PyTorch, Transformers, RL (MuJoCo), Computer Vision, NLP<br/>
          <strong>Robotics:</strong> ROS2, PyMyCobot, LeRobot, ORB-SLAM3, MuJoCo<br/>
          <strong>Infrastructure:</strong> Docker, MinIO, LakeFS, Prometheus, Grafana<br/>
          <strong>Mobile/Web:</strong> Flutter, React, Node.js, Firebase, Astro<br/>
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mt-10 mb-4">What I'm Looking For</h2>
        <p>
          I'm open to research engineer, ML systems, and robotics roles — anywhere that involves building
          intelligent systems that interact with the physical world. I'm especially interested in teams working on
          embodied AI, large-scale data infrastructure, or research tooling.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mt-10 mb-4">Get in Touch</h2>
        <p>
          Email is best for opportunities. LinkedIn for introductions. I also have a 
          <Link href="https://cal.com/jonathan-m-yugked" external>public booking link</Link> for calls.
        </p>
        <p>
          <Link href="mailto:muhirejonathan123@gmail.com">muhirejonathan123@gmail.com</Link> · 
          <Link href="https://github.com/Jonathan-321" external>GitHub</Link> · 
          <Link href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonathan-muhire-aa8b06184/" external>LinkedIn</Link>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
